---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import CtaFooter from '../../components/CtaFooter.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Governance & Observability — SAM Enterprise"
  description="Platform policies control what agents can do. Agent profiles standardize team configurations. Full audit trails track every session and tool call."
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="detail-hero">
      <div class="detail-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="container detail-hero-content">
        <a href="/enterprise/" class="back-link animate-on-scroll">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
          Enterprise
        </a>
        <span class="section-label animate-on-scroll">Governance & Observability</span>
        <h1 class="detail-title animate-on-scroll">
          Control what agents do.<br />
          <span class="gradient-text">See everything.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="detail-subtitle animate-on-scroll">
          Platform policies define what agents are allowed to do. Agent profiles standardize
          configurations across teams. Full audit trails track every session, tool call, and cost.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="divider" />

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container detail-content">
        <div class="detail-block animate-on-scroll">
          <h2>Platform Policies</h2>
          <p>
            SAM platform policies define rules, constraints, and delegation boundaries for agent behavior.
            Policies are injected into agent instructions so agents operate within the boundaries
            your team sets. Policies propagate to child tasks automatically — when one agent
            dispatches work to another, the child inherits the parent's policy set.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-block animate-on-scroll">
          <h2>Agent Profiles</h2>
          <p>
            Engineering leads create profiles that bundle an agent type, model, and configuration into
            a reusable template. Teams pick from approved profiles instead of configuring from scratch.
            New team members get a working setup immediately.
          </p>
          <p>
            When standards change (new model, different agent, updated system prompt), update the profile.
            Every future task uses the new configuration. No per-user migration needed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-block animate-on-scroll">
          <h2>Session Audit Trails</h2>
          <p>
            Agent sessions are recorded: what was requested, what the agent produced, and task lifecycle
            events (start, completion, failure). Project-scoped activity feeds give team leads
            visibility without requiring access to the agent's workspace.
            When using SAM-managed AI billing, token usage and cost are tracked per session.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-block animate-on-scroll">
          <h2>Admin Observability</h2>
          <p>
            The admin dashboard provides real-time and historical views of platform health:
          </p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Worker log streaming and error tracking</li>
            <li>VM agent health and heartbeat monitoring</li>
            <li>Cost monitoring with projections</li>
            <li>AI usage breakdowns by model and user</li>
            <li>Node and workspace lifecycle tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-block animate-on-scroll">
          <h2>Knowledge & Context Management</h2>
          <p>
            SAM's knowledge graph stores project context, user preferences, and organizational decisions
            that persist across agent sessions. Agents start every task with the context they need instead of
            rediscovering it from scratch. Knowledge is project-scoped and searchable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="detail-nav animate-on-scroll">
          <a href="/enterprise/security/" class="detail-nav-link">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
            Security Isolation
          </a>
          <a href="/enterprise/" class="detail-nav-link">
            Enterprise Overview
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="divider" />
    <CtaFooter />
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .detail-hero { position: relative; padding: 140px 0 60px; overflow: hidden; }
  @media (min-width: 768px) { .detail-hero { padding: 160px 0 80px; } }
  .detail-glow { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); width: 600px; height: 400px; background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.1) 0%, transparent 70%); pointer-events: none; }
  .detail-hero-content { max-width: 720px; }
  .back-link { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-fg-dim); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--color-fg-muted); }
  .detail-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4.5vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--color-fg-primary); margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .gradient-text { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent) 0%, var(--color-success) 100%); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
  .detail-subtitle { font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--color-fg-muted); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 600px; }
  .detail-content { max-width: 720px; }
  .detail-block { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .detail-block h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg-primary); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .detail-block p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-fg-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px; }

  .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .feature-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .detail-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px; padding-top: 32px; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); }
  .detail-nav-link { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-fg-muted); }
  .detail-nav-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
